    <h1 class='post__title__title mv025 noe theme__text' >The Road Map to Alien Life Passes Through the ‘Cosmic Shoreline’</h1>
    <div class='post__title__author-date h5 mt1'>
            <div class='byline relative flex flex-items-start merriweather mv025 mr1 gray3 h6t theme__text-hover'>
        <em class='byline__by gray4 mr075'>By </em>
                    <a href='https://www.quantamagazine.org/authors/elise-cutts/'>
                <span class='byline__author uppercase kern light small'>Elise Cutts</span>
            </a>
            </div>
<p class="h6 mv1 pv025 o6"><em>March 12, 2025</em></p>    </div>
    <div class='post__title__meta flex flex-wrap flex-items-start'>
        <div class='post__title__excerpt wysiwyg p italic mb1 mt025 pr2 o4 theme__text ' >
            Astronomers are ready to search for the fingerprints of life in faraway planetary atmospheres. But first, they need to know where to look — and that means figuring out which planets are likely to have atmospheres in the first place.        </div>
